sql:
SELECT document_type, COUNT(*) AS total_documents
FROM component_documents
GROUP BY document_type;

SELECT component_name
FROM components
WHERE category_id = (SELECT category_id FROM categories WHERE category_name = 'Transistor');

external_knowledge:
- "latest version details" refers to the most recent version number and description of a component; 
  - "maximum performance temperatures" refers to the highest temperature at which a component was tested; 
  - "latest documents" are the most recently added documents for each component.

- Write permission refers to the ability to modify or edit; 
- Associated documents imply that these components are involved in projects or tasks that have documentation; 
- SN74 performance value could be a specific metric related to the components' functionality or efficiency.

